cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on machine learning in an unsupervised setting, specifically on the problem of simultaneous sample and feature selection. The paper discusses a unified approach to tackle these two problems, which are often interleaved with each other. This suggests that the paper could belong to multiple sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
